amountPaid(address,uint256).details: Payment Client will reduce the total amount of tokens it will stock up by the given amount.This has to be called by a paymentProcessor.

params.amount_: amount of tokens that have been paid out.
params.token_: The token in which the payment was made.

buy(uint256,uint256).details: Redirects to the internal function `_buyOrder` by passing the sender's address and deposit amount.

params._depositAmount: The amount of collateral token depoisited.
params._minAmountOut: The minimum acceptable amount the user expects to receive from the transaction.

buyFor(address,uint256,uint256).details: Redirects to the internal function `_buyOrder` by passing the receiver address and deposit amount.

params._depositAmount: The amount of collateral token deposited.
params._minAmountOut: The minimum acceptable amount the user expects to receive from the transaction.
params._receiver: The address that will receive the bought tokens.

calculatePurchaseReturn(uint256).details: This function takes into account any applicable buy fees before computing the         token amount to be minted. Revert when `_depositAmount` is zero.

params._depositAmount: The amount of tokens deposited by the user.

returns.mintAmount: The amount of new tokens that will be minted as a result of the deposit.

calculateSaleReturn(uint256).details: Function uses the collateral sell fee from the payment processor             function processPayments() to calculate the sale return.             This is done because the collateral fee will be collected when the             payment processor executes the payment queue.

params._depositAmount: The amount of tokens deposited by the user.

returns.redeemAmount_: The amount of collateral that will be redeemed as a result of the deposit.

closeBuy().details: Only callable by the {Orchestrator_v1} admin.         Reverts if buying is already closed.

closeSell().details: Only callable by the {Orchestrator_v1} admin.         Reverts if selling is already closed.

collectPaymentOrders().details: Marks the orders as completed for the client.

params.amount_: The amount of collateral to deposit.

executeRedemptionQueue().details: If this function is called but the Payment Processor does not         implement the option to manually execute the redemption queue         then this function will revert.

returns.flags_: The flags this client will use.

returns.isDirectOnly_: Whether only direct operations are allowed.

returns.maxProjectSellFee_: The maximum project sell fee percentage.

returns.amount_: The total amount of open redemptions.

returns.treasury_: The address of the project treasury.

returns.role_: The queue executor role admin identifier

returns.buyPrice_: uint The static price for buying the issuance token.

returns.sellPrice_: uint The static price for selling the issuance token.

params.target: The target address to grant the role to.

params.targets: The target addresses to grant the role to.

identifier().details: The identifier is defined as the keccak256 hash of the module's         abi packed encoded major version, url and title.

init(address,(uint256,uint256,uint256,st.details: CAN be overridden by downstream contract.MUST call `__Module_init()`.

params.configData_: The config data of the module, comprised of:     - address: projectTreasury: The project treasury address.     - address: issuanceToken: The issuance token address.     - address: acceptedToken: The accepted token address.     - uint: buyFee: The project buy fee.     - uint: sellFee: The project sell fee.     - uint: maxSellFee: The maximum project sell fee.     - uint: maxProjectBuyFee: The maximum project buy fee.     - bool: isDirectOperationsOnly: Whether only direct operations       are allowed.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: We imitate here the EIP2771 Standard to enable metatransactions         As it currently stands we dont want to feed the forwarder address to each module individually and we decided to         move this to the orchestrator.

params.forwarder: The contract address to be verified.

returns._0: bool Is the given address the trusted forwarder.

openBuy().details: Only callable by the {Orchestrator_v1} admin.         Reverts if buying is already open.

openSell().details: Only callable by the {Orchestrator_v1} admin.         Reverts if selling is already open.

params.token_: The token in which to pay.

params.target: The target address to revoke the role from.

params.targets: The target addresses to revoke the role from.

sell(uint256,uint256).details: Redirects to the internal function `_sellOrder` by passing the sender's address and deposit amount.

params._depositAmount: The amount of issued token deposited.
params._minAmountOut: The minimum acceptable amount the user expects to receive from the transaction.

sellTo(address,uint256,uint256).details: This function wraps the `_sellOrder` internal function with specified parameters to handle         the transaction and direct the proceeds.

params._depositAmount: The amount of tokens to be sold.
params._minAmountOut: The minimum acceptable amount of proceeds that the receiver should receive from the sale.
params._receiver: The address that will receive the redeemed tokens.

setBuyFee(uint256).details: Only callable by the {Orchestrator_v1} admin.         The fee cannot exceed 10000 basis points. Reverts if an invalid fee is provided.

params.isDirectOperationsOnly_: The new value for the flag.

params.projectTreasury_: The address of the project treasury.

setSellFee(uint256).details: Only callable by the {Orchestrator_v1} admin.         The fee cannot exceed 10000 basis points. Reverts if an invalid fee is provided.

transferOrchestratorToken(address,uint25.details: This function MUST be restricted to be called only by the {Orchestrator_v1}.This function CAN update internal user balances to account for the new token balance.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be transfered.
params.to: The address that will receive the tokens.

trustedForwarder().details: We imitate here the EIP2771 Standard to enable metatransactions.         As it currently stands we dont want to feed the forwarder address to each module individually and we decided to         move this to the orchestrator.

params._amount: The amount of fee to withdraw.
params._receiver: The address that will receive the fee.

amountPaid(address,uint256).notice: Notifies the PaymentClient, that tokens have been paid out accordingly.

buy(uint256,uint256).notice: Buy tokens for the sender's address.

buyFor(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Buy tokens on behalf of a specified receiver address.

calculatePurchaseReturn(uint256).notice: Calculates the amount of tokens to be minted based on a given deposit amount.

calculateSaleReturn(uint256).notice: Calculates the amount of tokens to be redeemed based on a given deposit amount.

closeBuy().notice: Closes the buying functionality for the token.

closeSell().notice: Closes the selling functionality for the collateral.

depositReserve(uint256).notice: Allows depositing collateral to provide reserves for redemptions.

executeRedemptionQueue().notice: Manually executes the redemption queue in the workflows Payment         Processor.

getFlagCount().notice: Returns the number of flags this client uses for PaymentOrders.

getFlags().notice: Returns the flags used when creating payment orders in this         client.

getIsDirectOperationsOnly().notice: Gets the direct operations only flag.

getIssuanceToken().notice: Returns the address of the issuance token.

getMaxProjectBuyFee().notice: Gets the maximum fee that can be charged for buy operations.

getMaxProjectSellFee().notice: Gets the maximum project fee that can be charged for sell         operations.

getOpenRedemptionAmount().notice: Gets the current open collateral redemption amount.

getQueueExecutorRole().notice: Gets the queue executor role identifier

getQueueExecutorRoleAdmin().notice: Gets the queue executor role admin identifier

getStaticPriceForBuying().notice: Calculates and returns the static price for buying the issuance token.

getStaticPriceForSelling().notice: Calculates and returns the static price for selling the issuance token.

getWhitelistRoleAdmin().notice: Gets the whitelist role admin identifier

grantModuleRole(bytes32,address).notice: Grants a module role to a target address.

grantModuleRoleBatched(bytes32,address[].notice: Grants a module role to multiple target addresses.

isTrustedForwarder(address).notice: Checks if the provided address is the trusted forwarder.

openBuy().notice: Opens the buying functionality for the token.

openSell().notice: Opens the selling functionality for the collateral.

outstandingTokenAmount(address).notice: Returns the total outstanding token payment amount.

paymentOrders().notice: Returns the list of outstanding payment orders.

projectCollateralFeeCollected().notice: Accumulated project trading fees collected from deposits made by users         when engaging with the bonding curve-based funding manager. Collected in collateral.

revokeModuleRole(bytes32,address).notice: Revokes a module role from a target address.

revokeModuleRoleBatched(bytes32,address[.notice: Revokes a module role from multiple target addresses.

sell(uint256,uint256).notice: Redeem collateral for the sender's address.

sellTo(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Redeem tokens and directs the proceeds to a specified receiver address.

setBuyFee(uint256).notice: Sets the fee percentage for buying tokens, payed in collateral.

setIsDirectOperationsOnly(bool).notice: Toggles whether the contract only allows direct operations or not.

setSellFee(uint256).notice: Sets the fee percentage for selling collateral, payed in collateral.

transferOrchestratorToken(address,uint25.notice: Transfer a specified amount of Tokens to a designated receiver address.

withdrawProjectCollateralFee(address,uin.notice: Withdraw project collateral fee to the receiver address.
